snippet.textDisplay:
I'm reposting this because I just replied to someone else's post.


I've seen a few comments about why didn't John Legend and Steveie Wonder let Bill sing his own song?


If you guys knew anything about Bill, he wanted it this way. The man was so unassuming when he was honored that he wasn't even sure that he would perform at the Rockhall ceremonies. He never sought the headlines, and walked away from the business in 1985 because he didn't want to sell his ideals out for a buck.


If you don't believe me, check it out for yourself. We were just lucky to have him on stage in 2015, and were lucky to have him at all. He was a man for his time, and for all times.


RIP, soul man...you deserve your peace. Thank you for your stirring words and music. We are poorer without you, but richer because you lived.
